The need for speed Le Run is disputed throughout the Americas.
Revision
Originally, a problem-free race is transformed because of a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with a routine morning shift at work.
It fulfills to some extent everyone’s ambition but it’s useless if no one wants to do anything more.
The new subtitled The Run produced high expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the old Need for Speed racing series and to come out a kind of game from playable games that would not only count with points.
So we were curious what the added passages would be where the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already the case in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole shoots down due to a few unnecessary faults that already exist for several years.
These are not really mistakes, but rather the expression of an incomprehensible misunderstanding on the part of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are caught in the adventure of which the main hero Jack has character problems and to settle them begins to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has some interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
As a result, each race takes place on a different route and the planned steps in different environments that are quite different from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are especially pretty even though the graphical technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
After all, this is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very pleasant visually.
The tests are additionally occasionally accommodated with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly diminishes your visibility.
Then in the mountains you need to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
In addition to this, the different races are well organized one after the other.
There are only a small number of them, but that is enough.
There are moments when you try to exceed the number of opponents requested (as in a classic race) then you run against the watch (classic duel with the timer) and then another duel with an opponent awaits you.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and try to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the passages out of the vehicle.
This is rather an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by tapping on the right button at the right time.
It's not complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
As a result, this is how it is because this element does not risk disturbing and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that aggravate the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that at the moment there is nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said that it is negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you’ll have to go somewhere else.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of racing design.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
Unlike the model of driving, the model of collisions is not yet ready.
We do not expect complicated deformation and collisions from this game, but when you do not have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, so it is not completely good.
During tight overruns you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car starts out in crazy volts.
Or maybe he's in a mess.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really bothers you.
The restart is done in such a way that when you broke your figure or went out in the decor the game brings you back to the moment of the last point on the itinerary.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to restart the game from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go right, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes restarts don't help and you need to find the solution by remembering the piece of itinerary in question.
The great hiccup of this game is that the same actions are in the same places.
For example, there are certain bends that must be passed in a certain way or else it will not pass.
Otherwise you meet at a given location of "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds ahead or a minute late.
What makes you angry are the situations when you easily see the opponent passing between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and turn them or brake them.
It doesn’t matter if you go ahead of him because it is “calculated” in such a way that for the given situation it always happens very close to your nose.
The opponents have other advantages.
During the entire time of the game, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about the time, and you always have the same opponent who precedes you in the same place.
This gets the most upset at the end of the game when you ride on a long deck in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass in front of you at all costs.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you enter into collision a number of times.
One can understand that the purpose of this game is to do something captivating and full of adredalin, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that's going on.
And it doesn’t matter if it’s because of the concept of 50 unique itineraries, that the order of the races is such that there is no chance of getting bored or anything else.
The original idea is to change the car during the races.
You have to pay attention to gasoline pumps on the routes as you can change cars there however most of the time the one you have is enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, big American cylinders for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic atours on highly technical rides, for example on lace roads in the mountains.
And the challenge mode, which are races in particular places that you know about the adventure, goes very well with the main diet of the story.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
It connects online with the Autolog feature, which among other things compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other features in the community.
One of the hardest hits to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the roads (it looks like).
Your speed indicator shows you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you comes a subway that sends the car directly to the railroad.
In the editorial board we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought about creating this game or whether the authors really think we are idiots.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally nice and in some cases really great.
What is disturbing is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not hold the level and in some cases in a tragic way.
This is especially true of accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid imagery is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is at your choice.
In order to please as many as possible and especially the youngest audience a new soundtrack was created in the style "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for the music.
Need for Speed: The Run is really confusing.
If the game didn’t have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it's not over.
The fun is really good but prepare for mistakes typing in your eyes with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
The velvet students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from high schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts organized on November 17.
"Charles University has an important role in this festival."
"Among the choirs is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival is the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Classes concert which takes place with free admission on November 17 from 2 pm on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of Velvets" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady, during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as the one of the Charles University take place.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate with dignity the International Day of Students and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Cheers in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, social gatherings, a student event and other activities.
Interested parties will find all the information on the festival’s website www.festaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
The Czechs behave like negativists and eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically eroded the balance between the institutions"
"I didn't expect such a hard war."
"It will take 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all players get used to their new role," said Milena Vicenova, the Czech ambassador to the European Union.
When she succeeded in describing the various EU bodies and their relations in such an understandable and visible way that a large number of lecturers from Charles University's Faculty of Law could envy her, she showed how serious she takes her motto "understandable and open about Europe."
Ms Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new Permanent President of the European Council.
“From the beginning, the criticisms resonated that he’s fad, that he’s a leather round, that he can’t fulfill any mission, and I have to say that he took his breath away from everyone because he holds his role to perfection.”
“He is a man who knows how to listen to 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to take from Europe.”
She explained the new post of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy as part of an answer to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "What phone number should I call?", so as an important step towards unity and greater readability of the Union's policy to the States.
Nobody wants to ban us our syrecky (cooked pasta cheese that smells very strong)
Mrs Vicenova also mentioned the agenda that has lived, lived and will live in a time close to the European Council.
She has qualified the Czech Presidency as a success two years ago.
The Czechs have resolved the upward financial crisis, the gas crisis or have organized a Summit for an Eastern Partnership.
It called the fall of the government very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is very busy at the moment.
In the words of the Ambassador, "the activity has been full" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that continues to be resolved even now.
In addition, the new seventh budget of the Union must be approved, which is becoming very complicated due to the current economic situation.
As it would appear that the budget will be thin and with a view to savings, which branch will have priority, which countries will be helped the most, the least, everything is to be resolved in the context of future negotiations.
The Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For an understandable Europe".
“I really don’t like abbreviations, foreign words, jargons that nobody understands.
As the citizen must understand, it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted cornices, bananas that are different size or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky.”
It wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the European institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to the Ambassador, the Czechs have a reputation for being Eurosceptics and people who see things only in their negative aspect more than positively.
In addition, it is regrettable to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
The fault, according to her, is due to several factors, such as the shyness of our candidates, their inability to write a letter of motivation and poor support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech presidency, she then underlined the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when the Poles, the Magyars, the Slovaks come to me, this Frenchman says to me, 'Hey, what are you doing there, what is this Visegrad group still doing?' and he's not happy at all."
According to Mrs Vicenova, in the near future there are hard new rules on fiscal policy that await member countries.
It is the concept of a two-speed Europe, if not at multiple speeds, that prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
“We have countries in the eurozone and others outside the zone.”
"We have the Schengen area, we also have the enhanced cooperation institute."
In the first place, it was said that countries who want it co-operate with each other and those who do not want it remain in their corner."
"There will be many such institutes and there will be a really two-speed Europe," said Vicenova.
From this point of view, she also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the basis on which all the issues affecting the EU should be debated among all EU members and not just the memes of the eurozone.
History of a brand:
IBM Innovator Begins the Second Century of Its Existence
If someone had to look for the vocabulary that expresses IBM’s strategy as closely as possible, the closest would be “the long-term.”
For a wide audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has passed a hundred years.
The foundation of this long-term strategy was laid by the company’s first leader, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that a large number of global problems can be solved for as little as people are willing to think.
His motto “THINK!” has become the imprint around which the life of a future giant will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began to publish in 1935).
It was the basis of the company's culture carefully crafted by Watson.
For us, IBM means long-term thinking of continuous forward-looking movements.
IBM survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it still remained true to its core values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
This allowed us during our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, started to take care of his employees as Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM's people were the only among the first U.S. employees to have paid vacations, employer-paid insurance plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-developed reward system.
In the same way, IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
Society was at first brilliant in discovering talents—as one of the first firms to abolish any form of discrimination and thus could have the choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy as it will be a woman--Virginia Rometty--who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has been working at IBM for 30 years and currently holds the position of Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
In recent years, IBM has been doing what’s called jammy, online brainstorming, from which a lot of future strategies and innovations have emerged.
