After a thorough search in a larger area than the surrounding area, around the accident, no scattered parts of the aircraft were found, which supports the presumption that the impact took place in conditions of structural integrity.
MSS Announces Protocol to Find the Gene of Obesity
Social Security leads an investigation to discover the gene of obesity in the case of children and young people; this is supported by IPN specialists
The Mexican Institute of Social Security (IMSS) has announced that it is conducting an investigation to discover the gene of obesity in children and young people, called the protocol ‘Genetics of Obesity in Children and Adolescents’ that will have the markers associated with obesity.
In a statement, Miguel Cruz L<0xC3><0xB3>pez, head of the Medical Research Unit in Biochemistry at the Hospital of Specialties of the National Medical Center of the 20th Century, explained that a multidisciplinary team of doctors, nurses, nutritionists and social workers had been formed.
This team is supported by specialists and graduate students from the National Institute of Public Health (INSP) and the Centre for Advanced Research and Studies (Cinvestav) of the National Polytechnic Institute (IPN).
Participants are invited to participate in the investigation and to attend the IMSS Sports Units in Valle de México, where minors are tested every Saturday from 8:00 a.m.
He stressed that the protocol began in the Sports Unit Cuauhtémoc (Estado de México Poniente) and that from October 8, the activity takes place in the Sports Unit of Nezahualc<0xC3><0xB3>yolt (Estado de México Oriente).
After achieving the goal of gathering 500 or 600 minors, the study will continue in the Sports Unit Independencia (south of Distrito Federal) and finally in the Sports Unit Morelos (north of Distrito Federal).
He explained that the purpose of this research and the e-knowledge of the components and importance of genetics in relation to the development of obesity and identifying risk factors in Mexican children and young people to prevent the onset of chronic degenerative diseases.
As World Diabetes Day will be celebrated on November 14, he mentioned that the goal is to bring together three thousand children and young people between the ages of six and 14, with the consent and under the supervision of their parents, for the application of specific food questionnaires.
They will also be asked about their physical activity and their family history of heredity of their diseases, to avoid risk factors that trigger conditions such as diabetes or kidney failure.
He detailed that on Saturdays all participants will be applied to anthropometric measurements (weight, size, size circumference), blood pressure, determination of glucose levels, triglycerides, cholesterol and insulin levels and genetics (they are trying to identify people associated with intileb).
Cruz L<0xC3><0xB3>pez noted that this investigation is the result of health care professionals’ concern about the alarming weight gain in the case of minors.
"The 1999 and 2006 health surveys reported that in just six years there was a 77 percent increase in obesity in boys and 47 percent in girls; in terms of overweight, there was also a dramatic increase," said the IMSS specialist.
He pointed out that the justification for the search for markers is based on the fact that the population of the country is different from the others by its genetic history.
He reported that, on average, Mexicans have a 65 percent Indo-American heritage, 30 percent European and five percent African, and this condition is reflected in people associated with diabetes and overweight.
He explained that in general, the genetics of obesity translates into the inability to burn the excess energy consumed (calories), which is deposited in the form of fat.
The researcher explained that the direct benefit for the participants is the comprehensive assessment of children, which makes it possible to detect if they have a degree of overweight or obesity.
Ila even said that the presence of dark-colored wrinkles (acanthoses) on the neck and forearm indicates the likelihood of suffering from metabolic alterations and even pre-diabetes.
The information is managed in a confidential manner, doctors hand it over in writing to the parents, who are explained each of the measures and changes in lifestyle that they need to make to prevent diseases.
Cruz L<0xC3><0xB3>pez explained that there are three main components that cause overweight, obesity and other chronic conditions: sedentary, which is the lack of daily physical activity, stay in front of the TV for most of the day and use means of transport instead of walking on short distances.
Another reason is the high caloric intake, i.e. the highest consumption of sweet drinks, carbohydrates (sizes - meat paste to corn flour wrapped in corn leaves - bread, pizza, hamburgers, etc.) with a high content of fats and proteins in this protocol.
UNAM’s asphalt would avoid cassis
Rafael Herrera, a researcher at UNAM’s Faculty of Chemistry, develops modified asphalts with polymers to produce a mixture with better yield, regardless of environmental and temperature conditions
If the signals that the pavement were resolved, it would no longer be necessary to repair about 200,000 cassis each rainy season in the Metropolitan Area of Valle de México, warns Rafael Herrera N<0xC3><0xA1>jera, a researcher at the Faculty of Chemistry (FQ) of UNAM, who assured that if the pavement construction and maintenance process was completed, it would be rebuilt.
During his conference A technological opinion on cassis, organized within the framework of the International Year of Chemistry, he announced that the laboratory for which he is responsible develops modified asphalts with polymers to produce a mixture with characteristics similar to those of asphalt, but with high levels of mechanical resistance.
Herrera N<0xC3><0xA1>jera believed that this type of modified asphalt could be used in places where the climate is extremely hot, such as some northern cities of the country, to improve the yield, and therefore, the formation of cassis.
He explained that asphalt, the heavier part of petroleum, is a set of hydrocarbon molecules, molecules with a heavier molecular weight, called asphalts, and molecules with a low molecular weight, called malthenes, which together give its carave.
The viscoelastic behavior of the asphalt consists in the fact that at high temperatures, of nearly 180 degrees, it behaves like a liquid, at 120 degrees C its viscosity is very high and at 50 degrees C it has an almost solid state, while at very low temperatures, the asphalt becomes brittle, adding
This means that in the streets the resistance of asphalt is not uniform and changes during the day depending on environmental and temperature conditions, the chemical engineering specialist warns.
The FQ researcher observed that the streets of Ciudad de México in their majority were covered by a flexible pavement, composed of six layers of materials, the last three of which involve asphalt.
Among the more superficial layers is the asphalt layer, formed by small stones bathed in asphalt and subsequently compacted.
Each of the small stones that form the layer, he said, is bathed in asphalt.
When the vehicles pass through it by generating effort, it allows the forces to spread very well in the pavement.
If we had modified asphalt, it would spread better, according to chemical engineering.
On the asphalt layer, he says, one puts a last layer called a rolling layer, made of fine stone, that is, sand that is also bathed in asphalt.
As this is the layer in contact with the wheels of vehicles, it must have more mechanical force than the asphalt layer and provide grip in the street.
Being the part of the pavement that receives and distributes the effort, the bearing layer also requires that it has an adequate thickness and the material from which it is made must be treated.
Climate, especially humidity and temperature variations, are also a very important factor to consider, especially water, he says, as these significantly affect the yield of the asphalt layer.
When the soil is wet, the water spreads inside the layer it is difficult for it to come out, which softens all the layers of the pavement and therefore causes cassis.
In the process of forming a cassis, he says, the first that breaks is the rolling film and only later is affected the asphalt layer, but the damage does not take place immediately, but it is a process that must be treated at the first signals with adequate maintenance programs.
The member of the National System of Researchers explained that vehicle loading is another important factor for the formation of cassis and therefore the thickness of each layer of the pavement must always be linked to the loading of vehicles and ensure its satisfaction, in order to avoid the frequent formation of cassis.
Rafael Herrera warned that there is still much to investigate and work on asphalt, for example, bituminous emulsions, which in other countries already exist on the market and make it possible to repair the cassis easily and without having to use high temperatures.
